articles.title: ALL EYES ON IRAN'S RESPONSE AFTER US STRIKES NUCLEAR SITES
articles.description: Following US strikes on three Iranian nuclear sites, the world is closely watching for Iran's retaliation and the potential for further escalation in the Middle East. Various sources report on the immediate aftermath, international reactions, and the strategic implications of these attacks.

articles.title: Fred Smith, FedEx founder who revolutionized the package delivery business, dies at 80
articles.description: Fred Smith, the visionary founder of FedEx, has passed away at the age of 80. He is remembered for transforming the logistics industry and creating a global package delivery empire.

articles.title: Eastern half of U.S. braces for more long days of dangerous heat
articles.description: A brutal heat wave continues to blanket much of the eastern United States, with forecasts indicating several more days of dangerously high temperatures. Authorities are issuing warnings and advising residents on how to cope with the extreme conditions.
